```plantuml
@startuml Bytom-Community_Bytom-Server
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #ffffff
  BorderColor black
  Style roundrect
}
left to right direction

actor User

rectangle "Bytom Server" as BytomServer {
  rectangle "Blockchain Core" as BC #lightblue
  rectangle "Peer-to-Peer Networking" as P2P #lightyellow
  rectangle "Block Synchronization" as NetSync #lightgreen
  rectangle "Mining" as Mining #lightcoral
  rectangle "Data Store Abstraction" as DataStore #aliceblue
  rectangle "gRPC API" as GRPC #lavender
  rectangle "Transaction Handling" as TransactionHandling #lightpink
  rectangle "Bytom Virtual Machine" as VM #lightgoldenrodyellow
  rectangle "Wallet Functionality" as Wallet #lightsteelblue
}

User --> GRPC : interact with Bytom server\nvia RPC API

GRPC <--> BC : request blockchain data\n(e.g., blocks, transactions)
GRPC <--> Wallet : manage accounts\ncreate and sign transactions

P2P <--> BC : exchange blockchain data\n(e.g., blocks, transactions)
P2P <--> NetSync : synchronize blocks\nand transactions
P2P <--> Mining : distribute mining tasks

NetSync --> BC : update local blockchain\nwith synchronized data

Mining <--> BC : create block templates\nsubmit mined blocks

DataStore <--> BC : store and retrieve\nblockchain data

TransactionHandling <--> BC : validate and process\ntransactions
TransactionHandling --> VM : execute smart contracts

Wallet --> GRPC : manage wallets\nand keys

@enduml
```